# ETL cache (regeneratable — re-download via _etl_scripts/sync_hubspot.mjs etc.)
# Includes raw HubSpot API exports with stripe IDs and owner emails. Always
# stays local; ETL pulls fresh copies on demand.
_etl_scripts/cache

# Data snapshots — SOFT GATE (this week): committed so Vercel can serve them.
# Repo MUST remain private. Anyone with repo access can read this data.
# NEXT WEEK: migrate to Supabase Storage + build-time fetch, then re-add this
# line to keep snapshots out of the repo permanently.
#
# public/snapshots

# Financial / customer-specific config data — NEVER commit:
# - ebitda_adjustments.json has actual $ adjustment values
# - synthetic_transactions.json has off-Stripe payment $ amounts
# - transaction_overrides.json has per-transaction $ overrides
# - variance_overrides.json / annual_amortization_overrides.json — config that
#   ties to specific customers and may include amounts
# - churn_research_batches/* — per-customer evidence quotes + lifetime $
# - src/data/annual_payers.json has typical annual contract $ amounts
_etl_scripts/ebitda_adjustments.json
_etl_scripts/synthetic_transactions.json
_etl_scripts/transaction_overrides.json
_etl_scripts/variance_overrides.json
_etl_scripts/annual_amortization_overrides.json
_etl_scripts/churn_research_batches/
src/data/annual_payers.json

